{{DISPLAYTITLE:A_RestoreSpecialThing2}}
'''A_RestoreSpecialThing2'''

(no parameters)
{{Warning|text=This function should not be used. This article is for the purposes of complete documentation only.}}

Gives the calling actor the SPECIAL flag and, if it normally has it, restores the NOGRAVITY flag as well, then puts the calling actor back in its Spawn state. This, along with [[A_RestoreSpecialPosition]] and [[A_RestoreSpecialThing1]], is used by the engine to "respawn" pickup items that were "hidden" after pickup.

[[category:Decorate Internal functions]]{{DEFAULTSORT:RestoreSpecialThing2}}
